<h2>Contract</h2>
<p>
  The standard defines an injectable <strong>controller</strong> and a <strong>region element</strong> with
  observable events. Concrete timing, animation, and presentation live in the implementation (Frontier UI),
  not here.
</p>
{% highlight "typescript" %}
// Resolved from the injector chain; app code calls it imperatively.
interface NotificationController {
  // Enqueue a notification; returns its id. Shape mirrors the Feedback Intent.
  show(message: NotificationMessage): string;
  // Dismiss one (by id) or all currently shown/queued.
  dismiss(id?: string): void;
}

interface NotificationMessage {
  content: string | Node;          // what the user reads
  severity: 'info' | 'success' | 'warning' | 'error';   // shared severity vocabulary (Message Intent)
  duration?: 'short' | 'long' | 'indefinite';            // auto-timeout tier; defaults per impl
  action?: { label: string; intent: string };           // optional; forces duration -> indefinite
}

// The declarative top-layer host, placed once per app. Reads the Feedback Intent's
// placement (top-end, bottom-start, …) and stackLimit (1 = replace, >1 = FIFO stack).
// <notification-region placement="top-end" stack-limit="3"></notification-region>
{% endhighlight %}

<h3>Observable events</h3>
<ul>
  <li><code>notification-shown</code> — fired on the region when a notification becomes visible (detail: id, severity).</li>
  <li><code>notification-dismissed</code> — fired when one is removed (detail: id, reason: <code>timeout</code> | <code>manual</code> | <code>action</code> | <code>replaced</code>).</li>
</ul>

<h2>Behaviour</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Announcement (severity-mapped).</strong> The region is a live region; <code>info</code>/<code>success</code> → <code>role="status"</code> (polite), <code>warning</code>/<code>error</code> → <code>role="alert"</code> (assertive). Announced once on show; decoupled from visual persistence. Transport is the <a href="/intents/live-region-status/">Live-Region Status Intent</a>.</li>
  <li><strong>Queue / stack.</strong> <code>stackLimit = 1</code> replaces the current message; <code>&gt; 1</code> shows a FIFO stack up to the limit, surplus queued.</li>
  <li><strong>Timeout.</strong> <code>duration</code> drives auto-dismiss, <strong>paused</strong> while the pointer is over the region or focus is within it, and <strong>forced indefinite</strong> whenever an <code>action</code> is present.</li>
  <li><strong>Dismissal.</strong> Every notification is manually dismissable (a close affordance) and Escape-dismissable.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Composition</h2>
<p>
  Implements the <a href="/intents/feedback/">Feedback Intent</a>. Composes the
  <a href="/intents/message/">Message Intent</a> (shared severity/tone vocabulary), the
  <a href="/intents/live-region-status/">Live-Region Status Intent</a> (announcement), the
  <a href="/intents/surface/">Surface Intent</a> (card elevation/material), and the
  <a href="/intents/motion/">Motion Intent</a> (enter/exit). Presentation styles such as toast and snackbar
  are implementation choices over this contract, not dimensions of the standard.
</p>
